d chop <b>4 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add oil, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon and blend <b>4 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Transfer paste onto lamb and rub over entire shoulder. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place lamb onto a wire rack into roasting pan. Place lemon juice and 250 g of the water into base of pan and cover tightly with aluminium foil or a secure lid. Place into oven, reduce temperature to 160°C and roast for 2 hours (160°C). Check liquid levels and top up with an additional 250 g water, if needed. Roast for a further 2 hours (160°C). Increase oven temperature to 180°C. Remove lamb from oven, uncover and add fennel and potatoes into pan. Baste lamb with pan juices. Roast for a further 30 minutes (180°C), or until fennel and potatoes are tender and lamb is falling off the bone. Cover lamb and rest for a minimum of 15 minutes before serving."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Agrodolce"},{"content":"Place water, red wine vinegar and sugar into mixing bowl and cook <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add garlic and onions and chop <b>8 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add currants, fennel seeds, salt, pepper and balsamic vinegar and cook <b>30 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid."},{"content":"Add parsley and mint and blend <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer into a serving bowl."},{"content":"Garnish lamb with fennel fronds and mint; serve with roasted vegetables and agrodolce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To save time, ask your butcher to prepare the lamb for you.","Use the smallest potatoes you can find, or cut larger potatoes into cubes (2.5 cm).","Add 5 anchovies to lamb rub in step 2 for a rich, salty depth of flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","5h 15m","8 portions"]}